  ('h119', 'humor', 119, 'It could be that the purpose of your life is to serve as a warning to others.', 'Unknown'),
  ('h120', 'humor', 120, 'A good speech should be like a woman''s skirt: long enough to cover the subject and short enough to create interest.', 'Winston Churchill'),
  ('h121', 'humor', 121, 'First, I was afraid to die. Then I was afraid to live. Now I''m afraid to admit either of those things.', 'Unknown'),
  ('h122', 'humor', 122, 'Time flies like an arrow. Fruit flies like a banana.', 'Groucho Marx'),
  ('h123', 'humor', 123, 'My goal weight is for the scale to just give up and say ''One at a time please.''', 'Unknown'),
  ('h124', 'humor', 124, 'Life is short, so smile while you still have teeth.', 'Unknown'),
  ('h125', 'humor', 125, 'I asked my dog what two minus two is. He said nothing.', 'Unknown'),
  ('h126', 'humor', 126, 'Do not argue with an idiot. He will drag you down to his level and beat you with experience.', 'Greg King'),
  ('h127', 'humor', 127, 'Some people are like clouds. When they go away, it''s a brighter day.', 'Unknown'),
  ('h128', 'humor', 128, 'I''m reading a book about anti-gravity. It''s impossible to put down.', 'Unknown'),
  ('h129', 'humor', 129, 'I''m writing an autobiography. The title is: ''Who Cares?''', 'Unknown'),
  ('h130', 'humor', 130, 'I''m not clumsy. The floor just hates me, the table and chairs are bullies, and the walls get in my way.', 'Unknown'),
