  ('h136', 'humor', 136, 'My favorite machine at the gym is the vending machine.', 'Caroline Rhea'),
  ('h137', 'humor', 137, 'I have a lot of growing up to do.', 'Unknown'),
  ('h138', 'humor', 138, 'I didn''t text you. Vodka did.', 'Unknown'),
  ('h139', 'humor', 139, 'I am not arguing. I am simply explaining why I am right.', 'Unknown'),
  ('h140', 'humor', 140, 'My wife told me to stop acting like a flamingo. I had to put my foot down.', 'Unknown'),
  ('h141', 'humor', 141, 'Some days I amaze myself. Other days I look for my phone while holding it.', 'Unknown'),
  ('h142', 'humor', 142, 'If I''m not back in five minutes, just wait longer.', 'Ace Ventura'),
  ('h143', 'humor', 143, 'I dream of a better tomorrow, where chickens can cross the road and not be questioned about their motives.', 'Unknown'),
  ('h144', 'humor', 144, 'Life is too short to be serious all the time. So if you can''t laugh at yourself, call me. I''ll laugh at you.', 'Unknown'),
  ('h145', 'humor', 145, 'Birthdays are good for you. Statistics show that people who have the most live the longest.', 'Unknown'),
  ('h146', 'humor', 146, 'Behind every great man is a woman rolling her eyes.', 'Jim Carrey'),
  ('h147', 'humor', 147, 'I''m sick of following my dreams. I''m just going to ask them where they''re going and hook up with them later.', 'Mitch Hedberg'),
  ('h148', 'humor', 148, 'I looked up my family tree and found three dogs using it.', 'Rodney Dangerfield'),
  ('h149', 'humor', 149, 'I don''t jog. It makes the ice jump right out of my glass.', 'Martin Mull'),
  ('h150', 'humor', 150, 'If you''re not supposed to eat at night, why is there a light bulb in the refrigerator?', 'Unknown'),
  ('h151', 'humor', 151, 'I work hard because millions of people on welfare depend on me.', 'Unknown'),
  ('h152', 'humor', 152, 'To do is to be. To be is to do. Do be do be do.', 'Frank Sinatra'),
  ('h153', 'humor', 153, 'Think of how stupid the average person is, and realize half of them are stupider than that.', 'George Carlin'),
  ('h154', 'humor', 154, 'I was born to be a pessimist. My blood type is B negative.', 'Unknown'),
  ('h155', 'humor', 155, 'He knows nothing; and he thinks he knows everything. That points clearly to a political career.', 'George Bernard Shaw'),
  ('h156', 'humor', 156, 'If you think you can do a thing or think you can''t do a thing, you''re right.', 'Henry Ford (used humorously)'),
  ('h157', 'humor', 157, 'The secret of life is to appreciate the pleasure of being terribly, terribly deceived.', 'Oscar Wilde'),
  ('h158', 'humor', 158, 'I''m an early bird and a night owl — so I''m wise and I have worms.', 'Michael Scott'),
  ('h159', 'humor', 159, 'Never put off until tomorrow what you can do the day after tomorrow.', 'Mark Twain'),
  ('h160', 'humor', 160, 'I''m on the seafood diet: I see food, and I eat it.', 'Unknown'),
  ('h161', 'humor', 161, 'The sole purpose of a child''s middle name is so he can tell when he''s really in trouble.', 'Unknown'),
  ('h162', 'humor', 162, 'I''m not arguing, I''m just explaining why I''m right.', 'Unknown'),
  ('h163', 'humor', 163, 'I''m going to stand outside. So if anyone asks, I''m outstanding.', 'Unknown'),
  ('h164', 'humor', 164, 'When tempted to fight fire with fire, remember that the Fire Department usually uses water.', 'Unknown'),
  ('h165', 'humor', 165, 'Don''t cry because it''s over, smile because it happened. But also cry because you''re sad.', 'Unofficial follow-up to Dr. Seuss'),
  ('h166', 'humor', 166, 'My patience is like my phone battery: it runs out fast.', 'Unknown'),
  ('h167', 'humor', 167, 'Never lend books, for no one ever returns them; the only books I have in my library are books that other folks have lent me.', 'Anatole France'),
  ('h168', 'humor', 168, 'Do it today. It might be illegal tomorrow.', 'Unknown'),
  ('h169', 'humor', 169, 'To be sure of hitting the target, shoot first, and call whatever you hit the target.', 'Ashleigh Brilliant'),
  ('h170', 'humor', 170, 'I told my psychiatrist that everyone hates me. He said I was being ridiculous. Everyone hasn''t met me yet.', 'Rodney Dangerfield'),
  ('h171', 'humor', 171, 'Everyone is entitled to be stupid, but some abuse the privilege.', 'Unknown'),
  ('h172', 'humor', 172, 'My wife told me I had to stop acting like a penguin. I was devastated. I couldn''t stand it.', 'Unknown'),
  ('h173', 'humor', 173, 'The trouble with quotes on the internet is that it''s difficult to discern whether or not they are genuine.', 'Abraham Lincoln'),
  ('h174', 'humor', 174, 'The best time to plant a tree was 20 years ago. The second best time is now. I planted mine 10 years ago so I''m right on schedule.', 'Unknown (riffed from proverb)'),
  ('h175', 'humor', 175, 'I thought about being a plumber, but the work was too draining.', 'Unknown'),
  ('h176', 'humor', 176, 'I didn''t lose my mind. I sold it on eBay.', 'Unknown'),
  ('h177', 'humor', 177, 'Gravity is not just a good idea. It''s the law.', 'Unknown'),
  ('h178', 'humor', 178, 'I used to think I was indecisive. But now I''m not so sure.', 'Unknown'),
  ('h179', 'humor', 179, 'Before I got married I had six theories about bringing up children. Now I have six children and no theories.', 'John Wilmot'),
  ('h180', 'humor', 180, 'Do not take life too seriously. You will never get out of it alive.', 'Elbert Hubbard'),
  ('h181', 'humor', 181, 'I''m not lazy, I''m in power saving mode.', 'Unknown'),
  ('h182', 'humor', 182, 'If your parents never had children, chances are you won''t either.', 'Dick Cavett'),
  ('h183', 'humor', 183, 'A day without laughter is a day wasted.', 'Charlie Chaplin'),
  ('h184', 'humor', 184, 'I never feel more alone than when I''m trying to put sunscreen on my back.', 'Jimmy Kimmel'),
  ('h185', 'humor', 185, 'You know you''re getting old when you stoop to tie your shoelaces and wonder what else you could do while you''re down there.', 'George Burns'),
  ('h186', 'humor', 186, 'May the forces of evil become confused on the way to your house.', 'George Carlin'),
  ('h187', 'humor', 187, 'I''m not saying I''m Wonder Woman. I''m just saying no one has ever seen me and Wonder Woman in the same room together.', 'Unknown'),
  ('h188', 'humor', 188, 'I''m not weird. I''m limited edition.', 'Unknown'),
  ('h189', 'humor', 189, 'I tried to be normal once. Worst two minutes of my life.', 'Unknown'),
  ('h190', 'humor', 190, 'My wife and I were happy for twenty years. Then we met.', 'Rodney Dangerfield'),
  ('h191', 'humor', 191, 'I refuse to answer that question on the grounds that I don''t know the answer.', 'Douglas Adams'),
  ('h192', 'humor', 192, 'Procrastination is the art of keeping up with yesterday.', 'Don Marquis'),
  ('h193', 'humor', 193, 'If I won the award for laziness, I''d send somebody to pick it up for me.', 'Lew Lehrman'),
