  ('h195', 'humor', 195, 'The older I get, the more clearly I remember things that never happened.', 'Mark Twain'),
  ('h196', 'humor', 196, 'When your mother asks, ''Do you want a piece of advice?'' it is a mere formality. It doesn''t matter if you answer yes or no. You''re going to get it anyway.', 'Erma Bombeck'),
  ('h197', 'humor', 197, 'I can resist everything except temptation.', 'Oscar Wilde'),
  ('h198', 'humor', 198, 'Women want men who are sensitive, kind, and understanding. They don''t want a man who listens to them.', 'Unknown'),
  ('h199', 'humor', 199, 'Always borrow money from a pessimist. He doesn''t expect it back.', 'Unknown'),
  ('h200', 'humor', 200, 'Life is short. Buy the shoes.', 'Unknown'),
  ('a1', 'athletic', 1, 'It''s not whether you get knocked down, it''s whether you get up.', 'Vince Lombardi'),
  ('a2', 'athletic', 2, 'The more difficult the victory, the greater the happiness in winning.', 'Pelé'),
  ('a3', 'athletic', 3, 'Champions keep playing until they get it right.', 'Billie Jean King'),
  ('a4', 'athletic', 4, 'You are never really playing an opponent. You are playing yourself.', 'Arthur Ashe'),
  ('a5', 'athletic', 5, 'Hard work beats talent when talent doesn''t work hard.', 'Tim Notke'),
  ('a6', 'athletic', 6, 'You miss 100% of the shots you don''t take.', 'Wayne Gretzky'),
  ('a7', 'athletic', 7, 'Do not let what you cannot do interfere with what you can do.', 'John Wooden'),
  ('a8', 'athletic', 8, 'Pain is temporary. Quitting lasts forever.', 'Lance Armstrong'),
  ('a9', 'athletic', 9, 'It''s not the size of the dog in the fight, it''s the size of the fight in the dog.', 'Mark Twain (sports tradition)'),
  ('a10', 'athletic', 10, 'The will to win is important, but the will to prepare is vital.', 'Joe Paterno'),
  ('a11', 'athletic', 11, 'You have to expect things of yourself before you can do them.', 'Michael Jordan'),
  ('a12', 'athletic', 12, 'I''ve failed over and over and over again in my life. And that is why I succeed.', 'Michael Jordan'),
  ('a13', 'athletic', 13, 'The only way to prove that you''re a good sport is to lose.', 'Ernie Banks'),
  ('a14', 'athletic', 14, 'If you can believe it, the mind can achieve it.', 'Ronnie Lott'),
  ('a15', 'athletic', 15, 'What makes something special is not just what you have to gain, but what you feel there is to lose.', 'Andre Agassi'),
  ('a16', 'athletic', 16, 'Ask not what your teammates can do for you. Ask what you can do for your teammates.', 'Magic Johnson'),
  ('a17', 'athletic', 17, 'Set your goals high, and don''t stop till you get there.', 'Bo Jackson'),
  ('a18', 'athletic', 18, 'Do not let the fear of striking out hold you back.', 'Babe Ruth'),
  ('a19', 'athletic', 19, 'Push yourself again and again. Don''t give an inch until the final buzzer sounds.', 'Larry Bird'),
  ('a20', 'athletic', 20, 'The difference between the impossible and the possible lies in a man''s determination.', 'Tommy Lasorda'),
  ('a21', 'athletic', 21, 'I don''t count my sit-ups. I only start counting when it starts hurting.', 'Muhammad Ali'),
  ('a22', 'athletic', 22, 'It ain''t over ''til it''s over.', 'Yogi Berra'),
  ('a23', 'athletic', 23, 'Float like a butterfly, sting like a bee.', 'Muhammad Ali'),
  ('a24', 'athletic', 24, 'I hated every minute of training, but I said, ''Don''t quit. Suffer now and live the rest of your life as a champion.''', 'Muhammad Ali'),
  ('a25', 'athletic', 25, 'It''s hard to beat a person who never gives up.', 'Babe Ruth'),
  ('a26', 'athletic', 26, 'Obstacles don''t have to stop you. If you run into a wall, don''t turn around and give up.', 'Michael Jordan'),
  ('a27', 'athletic', 27, 'You can''t put a limit on anything. The more you dream, the farther you get.', 'Michael Phelps'),
  ('a28', 'athletic', 28, 'Just keep going. Everybody gets better if they keep at it.', 'Ted Williams'),
  ('a29', 'athletic', 29, 'Only he who can see the invisible can do the impossible.', 'Frank L. Gaines'),
  ('a30', 'athletic', 30, 'Make each day your masterpiece.', 'John Wooden'),
  ('a31', 'athletic', 31, 'Winning is not a sometime thing; it''s an all-time thing.', 'Vince Lombardi'),
  ('a32', 'athletic', 32, 'Age is no barrier. It''s a limitation you put on your mind.', 'Jackie Joyner-Kersee'),
  ('a33', 'athletic', 33, 'You were born to be a player. You were meant to be here. This moment is yours.', 'Herb Brooks'),
  ('a34', 'athletic', 34, 'One man practicing sportsmanship is far better than fifty preaching it.', 'Knute Rockne'),
  ('a35', 'athletic', 35, 'Excellence is the gradual result of always striving to do better.', 'Pat Riley'),
  ('a36', 'athletic', 36, 'Never give up! Failure and rejection are only the first step to succeeding.', 'Jim Valvano'),
  ('a37', 'athletic', 37, 'Today I will do what others won''t, so tomorrow I can accomplish what others can''t.', 'Jerry Rice'),
  ('a38', 'athletic', 38, 'I never left the field saying I could have done more to get ready and that gives me peace of mind.', 'Peyton Manning'),
  ('a39', 'athletic', 39, 'Sweat is the cologne of accomplishment.', 'Heywood Hale Broun'),
  ('a40', 'athletic', 40, 'Nobody who ever gave his best regretted it.', 'George Halas'),
  ('a41', 'athletic', 41, 'Show me a gracious loser and I''ll show you a failure.', 'Knute Rockne'),
  ('a42', 'athletic', 42, 'The secret of my success is that I always managed to live to fly another day.', 'Chuck Yeager'),
  ('a43', 'athletic', 43, 'You''re never a loser until you quit trying.', 'Mike Ditka'),
  ('a44', 'athletic', 44, 'My motto was always to keep swinging. Whether I was in a slump or feeling badly or having trouble off the field, the only thing to do was keep swinging.', 'Hank Aaron'),
  ('a45', 'athletic', 45, 'You have to do something in your life that is honorable and not cowardly if you are to live in peace with yourself.', 'Larry Brown'),
  ('a46', 'athletic', 46, 'Never let your head hang down. Never give up and sit down and grieve. Find another way.', 'Satchel Paige'),
  ('a47', 'athletic', 47, 'The five S''s of sports training are: stamina, speed, strength, skill, and spirit; but the greatest of these is spirit.', 'Ken Doherty'),
  ('a48', 'athletic', 48, 'Without self-discipline, success is impossible, period.', 'Lou Holtz'),
  ('a49', 'athletic', 49, 'It''s not the will to win that matters — everyone has that. It''s the will to prepare to win that matters.', 'Paul Bryant'),
  ('a50', 'athletic', 50, 'The principle is competing against yourself. It''s about self-improvement, about being better than you were the day before.', 'Steve Young'),
  ('a51', 'athletic', 51, 'Most people give up just when they''re about to achieve success. They quit on the one-yard line.', 'Ross Perot'),
  ('a52', 'athletic', 52, 'Number one is just to gain a passion for running. To love the morning, to love the trail, to love the pace on the track.', 'Pat Tyson'),
  ('a53', 'athletic', 53, 'You find that you have peace of mind and can enjoy yourself, get more sleep, and rest when you know that it was a one hundred percent effort that you gave.', 'Gordie Howe'),
  ('a54', 'athletic', 54, 'He who is not courageous enough to take risks will accomplish nothing in life.', 'Muhammad Ali'),
  ('a55', 'athletic', 55, 'Each week I strive to be better than who I was the week before.', 'Unknown'),
  ('a56', 'athletic', 56, 'Champions aren''t made in gyms. Champions are made from something they have deep inside them.', 'Muhammad Ali'),
  ('a57', 'athletic', 57, 'You are what you repeatedly do.', 'Aristotle (sports context)'),
  ('a58', 'athletic', 58, 'Success is where preparation and opportunity meet.', 'Bobby Unser'),
  ('a59', 'athletic', 59, 'If you have everything under control, you''re not moving fast enough.', 'Mario Andretti'),
  ('a60', 'athletic', 60, 'Talent wins games, but teamwork and intelligence wins championships.', 'Michael Jordan'),
  ('a61', 'athletic', 61, 'The only way to prove that you''re a good sport is to lose.', 'Ernie Banks'),
  ('a62', 'athletic', 62, 'Gold medals aren''t really made of gold. They''re made of sweat, determination, and a hard-to-find alloy called guts.', 'Dan Gable'),
  ('a63', 'athletic', 63, 'The difference between ordinary and extraordinary is that little extra.', 'Jimmy Johnson'),
  ('a64', 'athletic', 64, 'There may be people who have more talent than you, but there''s no excuse for anyone to work harder than you do.', 'Derek Jeter'),
  ('a65', 'athletic', 65, 'The way to success is to prepare for it and then wait. You prepare to win while waiting for the right opportunity.', 'Shaquille O''Neal (paraphrased)'),
  ('a66', 'athletic', 66, 'To be the best, you have to beat the best.', 'Unknown'),
  ('a67', 'athletic', 67, 'Don''t measure yourself by what you have accomplished, but by what you should have accomplished with your ability.', 'John Wooden'),
  ('a68', 'athletic', 68, 'I''ve got a theory that if you give 100 percent all of the time, somehow things will work out in the end.', 'Larry Bird'),
  ('a69', 'athletic', 69, 'The will to win is inside every champion.', 'Unknown'),
  ('a70', 'athletic', 70, 'How you respond to the challenge in the second half will determine what you become after the game.', 'Lou Holtz'),
  ('a71', 'athletic', 71, 'Somewhere behind the athlete you''ve become and the hours of practice and the coaches who have pushed you is a little girl who fell in love with the game and never lost the love. Play for her.', 'Mia Hamm'),
  ('a72', 'athletic', 72, 'Run when you can, walk if you have to, crawl if you must; just never give up.', 'Dean Karnazes'),
  ('a73', 'athletic', 73, 'There are no shortcuts to any place worth going.', 'Beverly Sills (sports tradition)'),
  ('a74', 'athletic', 74, 'Mental toughness is doing the right thing even when you don''t feel like it.', 'Unknown'),
  ('a75', 'athletic', 75, 'Success is not a destination but the road that you''re on.', 'Marty Robbins'),
  ('a76', 'athletic', 76, 'Effort is between you and you.', 'Ray Lewis'),
  ('a77', 'athletic', 77, 'There are only two options: make progress or make excuses.', 'Unknown'),
  ('a78', 'athletic', 78, 'Believe in yourself and all that you are. Know that there is something inside you that is greater than any obstacle.', 'Christian D. Larson'),
  ('a79', 'athletic', 79, 'Strength does not come from physical capacity. It comes from an indomitable will.', 'Mahatma Gandhi'),
  ('a80', 'athletic', 80, 'Winning takes talent; to repeat takes character.', 'John Wooden'),
  ('a81', 'athletic', 81, 'You were born to win, but to be a winner, you must plan to win, prepare to win, and expect to win.', 'Zig Ziglar'),
  ('a82', 'athletic', 82, 'The only place where success comes before work is in the dictionary.', 'Vince Lombardi'),
  ('a83', 'athletic', 83, 'One person can be a crucial ingredient on a team, but one person cannot make a team.', 'Kareem Abdul-Jabbar'),
  ('a84', 'athletic', 84, 'I always felt that my greatest asset was not my physical ability, it was my mental ability.', 'Bruce Jenner (Caitlyn Jenner)'),
  ('a85', 'athletic', 85, 'The mind is the limit. As long as the mind can envision the fact that you can do something, you can do it.', 'Arnold Schwarzenegger'),
  ('a86', 'athletic', 86, 'It''s not about how bad you want it. It''s about how hard you''re willing to work for it.', 'Unknown'),
  ('a87', 'athletic', 87, 'Without hard work, nothing grows but weeds.', 'Gordon B. Hinckley'),
  ('a88', 'athletic', 88, 'The groundwork of all happiness is health.', 'Leigh Hunt (sports tradition)'),
  ('a89', 'athletic', 89, 'Act like a champion. Train like a champion. Believe like a champion.', 'Unknown'),
  ('a90', 'athletic', 90, 'Do not be afraid to fail. Be afraid not to try.', 'Michael Jordan (paraphrased)'),
  ('a91', 'athletic', 91, 'If you fail to prepare, you''re prepared to fail.', 'Mark Spitz'),
  ('a92', 'athletic', 92, 'Persistence can change failure into extraordinary achievement.', 'Matt Biondi'),
  ('a93', 'athletic', 93, 'Every champion was once a contender who refused to give up.', 'Rocky Balboa (fictional)'),
  ('a94', 'athletic', 94, 'The difference between a successful person and others is not a lack of strength, not a lack of knowledge, but rather a lack of will.', 'Vince Lombardi'),
  ('a95', 'athletic', 95, 'Sports do not build character. They reveal it.', 'Heywood Hale Broun'),
  ('a96', 'athletic', 96, 'You have to train your mind like you train your body.', 'Bruce Jenner'),
  ('a97', 'athletic', 97, 'What to do with a mistake: recognize it, admit it, learn from it, forget it.', 'Dean Smith'),
  ('a98', 'athletic', 98, 'Be strong in body, clean in mind, lofty in ideals.', 'James Naismith (founder of basketball)'),
  ('a99', 'athletic', 99, 'Push your limits and break barriers.', 'Unknown'),
  ('a100', 'athletic', 100, 'There is no traffic jam along the extra mile.', 'Roger Staubach'),
  ('a101', 'athletic', 101, 'The true champions are those who never gave up.', 'Unknown'),
  ('a102', 'athletic', 102, 'How bad do you want it?', 'Unknown'),
  ('a103', 'athletic', 103, 'The last three or four reps is what makes the muscle grow. This area of pain divides a champion from someone who is not a champion.', 'Arnold Schwarzenegger'),
  ('a104', 'athletic', 104, 'Winning isn''t everything, but wanting to win is.', 'Vince Lombardi'),
  ('a105', 'athletic', 105, 'In athletics, there''s always been a willingness to accept success, but rarely the acknowledgment of failure.', 'Unknown'),
  ('a106', 'athletic', 106, 'Success is not about the destination; it''s about the journey.', 'Unknown'),
  ('a107', 'athletic', 107, 'A champion is someone who gets up when he can''t.', 'Jack Dempsey'),
  ('a108', 'athletic', 108, 'The key is not the will to win; everybody has that. It is the will to prepare to win that is important.', 'Bobby Knight'),
  ('a109', 'athletic', 109, 'Persistence is the twin sister of excellence. One is a matter of quality; the other, a matter of time.', 'Marabel Morgan'),
  ('a110', 'athletic', 110, 'To me, the biggest form of progress is the progressive overload in training.', 'Unknown'),
  ('a111', 'athletic', 111, 'The more I practice, the luckier I get.', 'Gary Player'),
  ('a112', 'athletic', 112, 'In sport, mental strength is as important as physical strength.', 'Unknown'),
  ('a113', 'athletic', 113, 'An athlete is not defined by their best performance, but by what they do when things go wrong.', 'Unknown'),
  ('a114', 'athletic', 114, 'Believe you can and you''re halfway there.', 'Theodore Roosevelt'),
  ('a115', 'athletic', 115, 'Nothing can stop the man with the right mental attitude from achieving his goal.', 'Thomas Jefferson'),
  ('a116', 'athletic', 116, 'There''s no such thing as a natural-born athlete. The greatest athletes are made, not born.', 'Unknown'),
  ('a117', 'athletic', 117, 'You don''t play against opponents. You play against the game of basketball.', 'Bobby Knight'),
  ('a118', 'athletic', 118, 'The difference between who you are and who you want to be is what you do.', 'Unknown'),
  ('a119', 'athletic', 119, 'Don''t wish for it. Work for it.', 'Unknown'),
  ('a120', 'athletic', 120, 'Pressure is a privilege — it only comes to those who earn it.', 'Billie Jean King'),
  ('a121', 'athletic', 121, 'It is not the size of the mountain but the magnitude of your perseverance that determines your summit.', 'Unknown'),
  ('a122', 'athletic', 122, 'The greatest gift you can give your team is a fully prepared leader.', 'Unknown'),
  ('a123', 'athletic', 123, 'To be the best, you need to train harder than the rest.', 'Unknown'),
  ('a124', 'athletic', 124, 'There is no substitute for hard work.', 'Thomas Edison (sports tradition)'),
  ('a125', 'athletic', 125, 'The body achieves what the mind believes.', 'Unknown'),
  ('a126', 'athletic', 126, 'On the field, you find out who you really are.', 'Unknown'),
  ('a127', 'athletic', 127, 'Discipline is the bridge between goals and accomplishment.', 'Jim Rohn'),
  ('a128', 'athletic', 128, 'Every strike brings me closer to the next home run.', 'Babe Ruth'),
  ('a129', 'athletic', 129, 'Pain is just weakness leaving the body.', 'Marine Corps motto'),
  ('a130', 'athletic', 130, 'You only get out of it what you put into it.', 'Unknown'),
  ('a131', 'athletic', 131, 'Sportsmanship is an attitude that strives for fair play, courtesy toward teammates and opponents, ethical behavior, and integrity.', 'Unknown'),
  ('a132', 'athletic', 132, 'The speed of the leader is the speed of the gang.', 'Unknown'),
  ('a133', 'athletic', 133, 'If you train hard, you''ll not only be hard, you''ll be hard to beat.', 'Herschel Walker'),
  ('a134', 'athletic', 134, 'Being challenged in life is inevitable, being defeated is optional.', 'Roger Crawford'),
  ('a135', 'athletic', 135, 'You can''t win unless you learn how to lose.', 'Kareem Abdul-Jabbar'),
  ('a136', 'athletic', 136, 'I play to win, whether during practice or a real game.', 'Michael Jordan'),
  ('a137', 'athletic', 137, 'What you get by achieving your goals is not as important as what you become by achieving your goals.', 'Zig Ziglar'),
  ('a138', 'athletic', 138, 'Without ambition one starts nothing. Without work one finishes nothing.', 'Ralph Waldo Emerson'),
  ('a139', 'athletic', 139, 'Courage is grace under pressure.', 'Ernest Hemingway (sports tradition)'),
  ('a140', 'athletic', 140, 'Go hard or go home.', 'Unknown (sports tradition)'),
  ('a141', 'athletic', 141, 'Mediocrity is the enemy of greatness.', 'Unknown'),
  ('a142', 'athletic', 142, 'The road to Easy Street goes through the sewer.', 'John Madden'),
  ('a143', 'athletic', 143, 'There are no limitations to the mind except those we acknowledge.', 'Napoleon Hill'),
  ('a144', 'athletic', 144, 'Persistence overrides talent, every time.', 'Unknown'),
  ('a145', 'athletic', 145, 'First master the fundamentals.', 'Larry Bird'),
  ('a146', 'athletic', 146, 'In training, you listen to your body. In competition, you tell your body to shut up.', 'Rich Froning'),
  ('a147', 'athletic', 147, 'The only impossible journey is the one you never begin.', 'Tony Robbins (sports tradition)'),
  ('a148', 'athletic', 148, 'Motivation gets you started. Habit keeps you going.', 'Jim Ryun'),
  ('a149', 'athletic', 149, 'Character is what you do when no one is watching.', 'John Wooden'),
  ('a150', 'athletic', 150, 'The greatest competition is with yourself.', 'Unknown'),
  ('a151', 'athletic', 151, 'Excellence is never an accident.', 'Aristotle (sports tradition)'),
  ('a152', 'athletic', 152, 'A trophy carries dust. Memories last forever.', 'Mary Lou Retton'),
  ('a153', 'athletic', 153, 'Working hard is important. But there is something that matters even more — believing in yourself.', 'Harry Potter (J.K. Rowling)'),
  ('a154', 'athletic', 154, 'Run the day. Don''t let the day run you.', 'Jim Rohn (sports context)'),
  ('a155', 'athletic', 155, 'There are no shortcuts to any place worth going.', 'Unknown'),
  ('a156', 'athletic', 156, 'Concentration is the ability to think about absolutely nothing when it is absolutely necessary.', 'Ray Knight'),
  ('a157', 'athletic', 157, 'True champions aren''t always the ones that win, but those with the most guts.', 'Mia Hamm'),
  ('a158', 'athletic', 158, 'In the middle of every difficulty lies opportunity.', 'Albert Einstein (sports tradition)'),
  ('a159', 'athletic', 159, 'There is no glory in practice, but without practice, there is no glory.', 'Unknown'),
  ('a160', 'athletic', 160, 'The secret is to work less as individuals and more as a team.', 'Knute Rockne'),
  ('a161', 'athletic', 161, 'Adversity causes some men to break and others to break records.', 'William Arthur Ward'),
  ('a162', 'athletic', 162, 'Don''t be afraid of failure. This is the way to succeed.', 'LeBron James'),
  ('a163', 'athletic', 163, 'No pain, no gain.', 'Jane Fonda'),
  ('a164', 'athletic', 164, 'An athlete must have fire in them. Desire alone isn''t enough. You''ve got to have the fire.', 'Jesse Owens'),
  ('a165', 'athletic', 165, 'Be willing to sacrifice what you are for what you could become.', 'Unknown'),
  ('a166', 'athletic', 166, 'Your biggest challenge isn''t someone else. It''s the ache in your lungs and the burning in your legs, and the voice inside you that yells ''can''t.'' But you don''t listen.', 'Unknown'),
  ('a167', 'athletic', 167, 'Success is the result of hard work, perseverance, learning, studying, sacrifice, and most of all, love of what you are doing.', 'Pelé'),
  ('a168', 'athletic', 168, 'The only way to do great work is to love what you do.', 'Steve Jobs (sports tradition)'),
  ('a169', 'athletic', 169, 'It is your attitude, not your aptitude, that will determine your altitude.', 'Zig Ziglar'),
  ('a170', 'athletic', 170, 'When you are not practicing, someone else is getting better.', 'Allen Iverson'),
  ('a171', 'athletic', 171, 'Winners never quit, and quitters never win.', 'Vince Lombardi'),
  ('a172', 'athletic', 172, 'The secret to success is to start from scratch and keep on scratching.', 'Dennis Green'),
  ('a173', 'athletic', 173, 'You may not be there yet, but you are closer than you were yesterday.', 'Unknown'),
  ('a174', 'athletic', 174, 'Keep your feet on the ground and keep reaching for the stars.', 'Casey Kasem (sports tradition)'),
  ('a175', 'athletic', 175, 'You can''t get much done in life if you only work on the days when you feel good.', 'Jerry West'),
  ('a176', 'athletic', 176, 'Concentrate all your thoughts upon the work in hand. The sun''s rays do not burn until brought to a focus.', 'Alexander Graham Bell (sports tradition)'),
  ('a177', 'athletic', 177, 'It''s supposed to be hard. If it wasn''t hard, everyone would do it. The hard is what makes it great.', 'Tom Hanks (A League of Their Own)'),
  ('a178', 'athletic', 178, 'Life is not measured by the number of breaths you take, but by the moments that take your breath away.', 'Maya Angelou (sports tradition)'),
  ('a179', 'athletic', 179, 'I am building a fire, and everyday I train, I add more fuel. At just the right moment, I light the match.', 'Mia Hamm'),
  ('a180', 'athletic', 180, 'Success doesn''t come from what you do occasionally. It comes from what you do consistently.', 'Marie Forleo (sports tradition)'),
  ('a181', 'athletic', 181, 'Champions are everywhere. All you need is to train them properly.', 'Arthur Lydiard'),
  ('a182', 'athletic', 182, 'The will to win, the desire to succeed, the urge to reach your full potential: these are the keys that will unlock the door to personal excellence.', 'Confucius'),
  ('a183', 'athletic', 183, 'Tough times never last, but tough people do.', 'Robert H. Schuller (sports tradition)'),
  ('a184', 'athletic', 184, 'Success is not measured by what you accomplish, but by the opposition you have encountered and the courage with which you have maintained the struggle.', 'Orison Swett Marden'),
  ('a185', 'athletic', 185, 'My goal is not to be better than anyone else, but to be better than I used to be.', 'Wayne Dyer (sports context)'),
  ('a186', 'athletic', 186, 'I may not have the biggest stats, but no one will outwork me.', 'Unknown'),
  ('a187', 'athletic', 187, 'There is no ''I'' in team, but there is an ''I'' in win.', 'Michael Jordan'),
  ('a188', 'athletic', 188, 'It always seems impossible until it''s done.', 'Nelson Mandela (sports tradition)'),
  ('a189', 'athletic', 189, 'Nothing is over until we decide it is.', 'John Rambo (fictional, sports tradition)'),
  ('a190', 'athletic', 190, 'Ability is what you''re capable of doing. Motivation determines what you do. Attitude determines how well you do it.', 'Lou Holtz'),
  ('a191', 'athletic', 191, 'The greatest oak was once a little nut who held its ground.', 'Unknown (sports tradition)'),
  ('a192', 'athletic', 192, 'You have to believe in yourself when no one else does.', 'Serena Williams'),
  ('a193', 'athletic', 193, 'It never gets easier, you just get better.', 'Unknown'),
  ('a194', 'athletic', 194, 'Hard work pays off in the future. Laziness pays off now.', 'Steven Wright (in jest, sports flip)'),
  ('a195', 'athletic', 195, 'Sweat, sacrifice, and success.', 'Unknown'),
  ('a196', 'athletic', 196, 'Your talent determines what you can do. Your motivation determines how much you are willing to do. Your attitude determines how well you do it.', 'Lou Holtz'),
  ('a197', 'athletic', 197, 'Every morning in Africa, a gazelle wakes up. It knows it must outrun the fastest lion, or it will be killed. Every morning in Africa, a lion wakes up. It knows it must run faster than the slowest gazelle, or it will starve. It doesn''t matter whether you''re the lion or a gazelle: when the sun comes up, you''d better be running.', 'Christopher McDougall (paraphrased African proverb)'),
  ('a198', 'athletic', 198, 'All athletes are disciplined. Not all are champions.', 'Unknown'),
  ('a199', 'athletic', 199, 'Defeat is not the worst of failures. Not to have tried is the true failure.', 'George Edward Woodberry'),
  ('a200', 'athletic', 200, 'The harder the battle, the sweeter the victory.', 'Les Brown'),
  ('r1', 'creative', 1, 'Creativity is intelligence having fun.', 'Albert Einstein'),
  ('r2', 'creative', 2, 'You can''t use up creativity. The more you use, the more you have.', 'Maya Angelou'),
  ('r3', 'creative', 3, 'Imagination is more important than knowledge.', 'Albert Einstein'),
  ('r4', 'creative', 4, 'Every artist was first an amateur.', 'Ralph Waldo Emerson'),
  ('r5', 'creative', 5, 'Art enables us to find ourselves and lose ourselves at the same time.', 'Thomas Merton'),
  ('r6', 'creative', 6, 'Creativity is not a talent. It is a way of operating.', 'John Cleese'),
  ('r7', 'creative', 7, 'An idea that is not dangerous is unworthy of being called an idea at all.', 'Oscar Wilde'),
  ('r8', 'creative', 8, 'The painter has the Universe in his mind and hands.', 'Leonardo da Vinci'),
  ('r9', 'creative', 9, 'To create is to live twice.', 'Albert Camus'),
  ('r10', 'creative', 10, 'The world always seems brighter when you''ve just made something that wasn''t there before.', 'Neil Gaiman'),
  ('r11', 'creative', 11, 'Logic will get you from A to Z; imagination will get you everywhere.', 'Albert Einstein'),
  ('r12', 'creative', 12, 'We are all creative, but by the time we are three or four years old, someone has knocked the creativity out of us.', 'Maya Lin (paraphrased)'),
  ('r13', 'creative', 13, 'Others have seen what is and asked why. I have seen what could be and asked why not.', 'Pablo Picasso'),
  ('r14', 'creative', 14, 'Inspiration exists, but it has to find you working.', 'Pablo Picasso'),
  ('r15', 'creative', 15, 'I saw the angel in the marble and carved until I set him free.', 'Michelangelo'),
  ('r16', 'creative', 16, 'An artist''s only concern is to shoot for some kind of perfection, and on his own terms, not anyone else''s.', 'J.D. Salinger'),
  ('r17', 'creative', 17, 'The worst enemy to creativity is self-doubt.', 'Sylvia Plath'),
  ('r18', 'creative', 18, 'Creativity takes courage.', 'Henri Matisse'),
  ('r19', 'creative', 19, 'Art is not what you see, but what you make others see.', 'Edgar Degas'),
  ('r20', 'creative', 20, 'The secret is there is no secret.', 'Unknown (creativity tradition)'),
  ('r21', 'creative', 21, 'Design is thinking made visual.', 'Saul Bass'),
  ('r22', 'creative', 22, 'You can''t wait for inspiration. You have to go after it with a club.', 'Jack London'),
  ('r23', 'creative', 23, 'A writer only begins a book. A reader finishes it.', 'Samuel Johnson'),
  ('r24', 'creative', 24, 'If you hear a voice within you say you cannot paint, then by all means paint, and that voice will be silenced.', 'Vincent Van Gogh'),
  ('r25', 'creative', 25, 'To practice any art, no matter how well or badly, is a way to make your soul grow. So do it.', 'Kurt Vonnegut'),
  ('r26', 'creative', 26, 'Every child is an artist. The problem is how to remain an artist once we grow up.', 'Pablo Picasso'),
  ('r27', 'creative', 27, 'The difference between a stumbling block and a stepping stone is how high you raise your foot.', 'Unknown (creative tradition)'),
  ('r28', 'creative', 28, 'Great things are done by a series of small things brought together.', 'Vincent Van Gogh'),
  ('r29', 'creative', 29, 'Art is the lie that enables us to realize the truth.', 'Pablo Picasso'),
  ('r30', 'creative', 30, 'Creativity is the power to connect the seemingly unconnected.', 'William Plomer'),
  ('r31', 'creative', 31, 'Don''t think. Thinking is the enemy of creativity.', 'Ray Bradbury'),
  ('r32', 'creative', 32, 'The creative act is not performed by the artist alone; the spectator brings the work in contact with the external world.', 'Marcel Duchamp'),
  ('r33', 'creative', 33, 'Read a thousand books, and your words will flow like a river.', 'Lisa See'),
  ('r34', 'creative', 34, 'The secret of all art is love.', 'Stendhal'),
  ('r35', 'creative', 35, 'Fiction is the truth inside the lie.', 'Stephen King'),
  ('r36', 'creative', 36, 'Start where you are. Use what you have. Do what you can.', 'Arthur Ashe (creative tradition)'),
  ('r37', 'creative', 37, 'To design is to communicate clearly by whatever means you can control or master.', 'Milton Glaser'),
  ('r38', 'creative', 38, 'Writing about a writer''s block is better than not writing at all.', 'Charles Bukowski'),
  ('r39', 'creative', 39, 'Without deviation from the norm, progress is not possible.', 'Frank Zappa'),
  ('r40', 'creative', 40, 'You see things; and you say, ''Why?'' But I dream things that never were; and I say, ''Why not?''', 'George Bernard Shaw'),
  ('r41', 'creative', 41, 'There is nothing new under the sun, but there are new suns.', 'Octavia Butler'),
  ('r42', 'creative', 42, 'If you want to build a ship, don''t drum up people together to collect wood and assign them tasks and work, but rather teach them to long for the endless immensity of the sea.', 'Antoine de Saint-Exupéry'),
  ('r43', 'creative', 43, 'The object of art is not to reproduce reality, but to create a reality of the same intensity.', 'Alberto Giacometti'),
  ('r44', 'creative', 44, 'I am enough of an artist to draw freely upon my imagination.', 'Albert Einstein'),
  ('r45', 'creative', 45, 'Begin anywhere.', 'John Cage'),
  ('r46', 'creative', 46, 'Think left and think right and think low and think high.', 'Dr. Seuss'),
  ('r47', 'creative', 47, 'Make visible what, without you, might perhaps never have been seen.', 'Robert Bresson'),
  ('r48', 'creative', 48, 'Creative minds are rarely tidy.', 'Unknown'),
  ('r49', 'creative', 49, 'Don''t tell me the moon is shining; show me the glint of light on broken glass.', 'Anton Chekhov'),
  ('r50', 'creative', 50, 'The creation of something new is not accomplished by the intellect but by the play instinct.', 'Carl Jung'),
  ('r51', 'creative', 51, 'Limitations live only in our minds. But if we use our imaginations, our possibilities become limitless.', 'Jamie Paolinetti'),
  ('r52', 'creative', 52, 'The most beautiful experience we can have is the mysterious. It is the fundamental emotion which stands at the cradle of true art and true science.', 'Albert Einstein'),
  ('r53', 'creative', 53, 'Every act of creation is first an act of destruction.', 'Pablo Picasso'),
  ('r54', 'creative', 54, 'We make our world significant by the courage of our questions and the depth of our answers.', 'Carl Sagan'),
  ('r55', 'creative', 55, 'There is only one way to avoid criticism: do nothing, say nothing, and be nothing.', 'Aristotle'),
  ('r56', 'creative', 56, 'You can never solve a problem on the level on which it was created.', 'Albert Einstein'),
  ('r57', 'creative', 57, 'Drawing is the honesty of the art. There is no possibility of cheating. It is either good or bad.', 'Salvador Dalí'),
  ('r58', 'creative', 58, 'An empty canvas is a living wonder, far lovelier than certain pictures.', 'Wassily Kandinsky'),
  ('r59', 'creative', 59, 'Art does not reproduce what we see; rather, it makes us see.', 'Paul Klee'),
  ('r60', 'creative', 60, 'The main thing is to be moved, to love, to hope, to tremble, to live.', 'Auguste Rodin'),
  ('r61', 'creative', 61, 'The job of the artist is always to deepen the mystery.', 'Francis Bacon'),
  ('r62', 'creative', 62, 'Mistakes are the portals of discovery.', 'James Joyce'),
  ('r63', 'creative', 63, 'You are the one who decides how far you go with your art.', 'Unknown'),
  ('r64', 'creative', 64, 'Color is my day-long obsession, joy, and torment.', 'Claude Monet'),
  ('r65', 'creative', 65, 'Life beats down and crushes the soul and art reminds you that you have one.', 'Stella Adler'),
  ('r66', 'creative', 66, 'Writing is easy. All you have to do is cross out the wrong words.', 'Mark Twain'),
  ('r67', 'creative', 67, 'The role of a writer is not to say what we all can say, but what we are unable to say.', 'Anaïs Nin'),
  ('r68', 'creative', 68, 'I write to give myself strength. I write to be the characters that I am not. I write to explore all the things I''m afraid of.', 'Joss Whedon'),
  ('r69', 'creative', 69, 'If you can dream it, you can do it.', 'Walt Disney'),
  ('r70', 'creative', 70, 'It is better to fail in originality than to succeed in imitation.', 'Herman Melville'),
  ('r71', 'creative', 71, 'In the world of art, the most dangerous thing is the mediocre.', 'Unknown'),
  ('r72', 'creative', 72, 'Vulnerability is the birthplace of innovation, creativity, and change.', 'Brené Brown'),
  ('r73', 'creative', 73, 'There is no greater agony than bearing an untold story inside you.', 'Maya Angelou'),
  ('r74', 'creative', 74, 'Whatever you can do or dream you can do, begin it. Boldness has genius, power, and magic in it.', 'Johann Wolfgang von Goethe'),
  ('r75', 'creative', 75, 'Creativity requires the courage to let go of certainties.', 'Erich Fromm'),
  ('r76', 'creative', 76, 'A poem begins as a lump in the throat, a sense of wrong, a homesickness, a lovesickness.', 'Robert Frost'),
  ('r77', 'creative', 77, 'The moment you doubt whether you can fly, you cease for ever to be able to do it.', 'J.M. Barrie'),
  ('r78', 'creative', 78, 'You don''t have to be great to start, but you have to start to be great.', 'Zig Ziglar (creative tradition)'),
  ('r79', 'creative', 79, 'The highest form of creativity is love.', 'Unknown'),
  ('r80', 'creative', 80, 'Style is knowing who you are, what you want to say, and not giving a damn.', 'Orson Welles'),
  ('r81', 'creative', 81, 'I am always doing that which I cannot do, in order that I may learn how to do it.', 'Pablo Picasso'),
  ('r82', 'creative', 82, 'Design is not just what it looks like and feels like. Design is how it works.', 'Steve Jobs'),
  ('r83', 'creative', 83, 'Make it simple but significant.', 'Don Draper (Mad Men)'),
  ('r84', 'creative', 84, 'Truth is stranger than fiction, but it is because Fiction is obliged to stick to possibilities; Truth isn''t.', 'Mark Twain'),
  ('r85', 'creative', 85, 'Originality is the art of concealing your source.', 'Franklin P. Jones'),
  ('r86', 'creative', 86, 'A creative man is motivated by the desire to achieve, not by the desire to beat others.', 'Ayn Rand'),
  ('r87', 'creative', 87, 'Curiosity is the wick in the candle of learning.', 'William Arthur Ward (creative tradition)'),
  ('r88', 'creative', 88, 'The greatest poet is one whose life is a poem.', 'Henry David Thoreau'),
  ('r89', 'creative', 89, 'One must always have one''s boots on, and be ready to leave.', 'Michel de Montaigne (creative tradition)'),
  ('r90', 'creative', 90, 'The only artist I have ever known who could walk on two legs was Leonardo da Vinci, and he was an exception.', 'Pablo Picasso (paraphrased)'),
  ('r91', 'creative', 91, 'Creativity is allowing yourself to make mistakes. Art is knowing which ones to keep.', 'Scott Adams'),
  ('r92', 'creative', 92, 'Genius is one percent inspiration, ninety-nine percent perspiration.', 'Thomas Edison'),
  ('r93', 'creative', 93, 'The hardest part is beginning.', 'Unknown'),
  ('r94', 'creative', 94, 'The arts are not a way to make a living. They are a very human way of making life more bearable.', 'Kurt Vonnegut'),
  ('r95', 'creative', 95, 'An artist must never be a prisoner of himself, prisoner of a style, prisoner of a reputation.', 'Henri Matisse'),
  ('r96', 'creative', 96, 'Do not go where the path may lead, go instead where there is no path and leave a trail.', 'Ralph Waldo Emerson'),
  ('r97', 'creative', 97, 'Every exit is an entry somewhere else.', 'Tom Stoppard'),
  ('r98', 'creative', 98, 'There are only two ways to live your life: one is as though nothing is a miracle, the other is as though everything is a miracle.', 'Albert Einstein'),
  ('r99', 'creative', 99, 'All great deeds and all great thoughts have a ridiculous beginning.', 'Albert Camus'),
  ('r100', 'creative', 100, 'Art washes away from the soul the dust of everyday life.', 'Pablo Picasso'),
  ('r101', 'creative', 101, 'The fear of making mistakes is a mistake in itself.', 'Unknown'),
  ('r102', 'creative', 102, 'If we knew what it was we were doing, it would not be called research, would it?', 'Albert Einstein (creative context)'),
  ('r103', 'creative', 103, 'A writer should not tell you a thing. She should let it be written in the sky.', 'Unknown'),
  ('r104', 'creative', 104, 'Ideas are the beginning of all achievement.', 'Bruce Lee'),
  ('r105', 'creative', 105, 'A musician must make music, an artist must paint, a poet must write, if he is to be at peace with himself.', 'Abraham Maslow'),
  ('r106', 'creative', 106, 'Words have no power to impress the mind without the exquisite horror of their reality.', 'Edgar Allan Poe'),
  ('r107', 'creative', 107, 'Write what should not be forgotten.', 'Isabel Allende'),
  ('r108', 'creative', 108, 'Talent hits a target no one else can hit; Genius hits a target no one else can see.', 'Arthur Schopenhauer'),
  ('r109', 'creative', 109, 'Poetry is what happens when nothing else can.', 'Charles Bukowski'),
  ('r110', 'creative', 110, 'I try to apply colors like words that shape poems, like notes that shape music.', 'Joan Miró'),
  ('r111', 'creative', 111, 'Perfectionism is the enemy of creation, as extreme cold is the enemy of life.', 'John Updike'),
  ('r112', 'creative', 112, 'Art is the signature of civilizations.', 'Beverly Sills'),
  ('r113', 'creative', 113, 'Creativity comes from a conflict of ideas.', 'Donatella Versace'),
  ('r114', 'creative', 114, 'There are three rules for writing a novel. Unfortunately, no one knows what they are.', 'W. Somerset Maugham'),
  ('r115', 'creative', 115, 'You don''t have to be an artist to have a creative mind.', 'Unknown'),
  ('r116', 'creative', 116, 'The creative process is a process of surrender, not control.', 'Julia Cameron'),
  ('r117', 'creative', 117, 'Creativity is just connecting things.', 'Steve Jobs'),
  ('r118', 'creative', 118, 'The role of art is to make a world which can be felt.', 'Pauline Kael'),
  ('r119', 'creative', 119, 'We don''t make mistakes, just happy little accidents.', 'Bob Ross'),
  ('r120', 'creative', 120, 'The greatest innovation will come from those who dare to play.', 'Unknown'),
  ('r121', 'creative', 121, 'Don''t be afraid to give up the good to go for the great.', 'John D. Rockefeller (creative tradition)'),
  ('r122', 'creative', 122, 'I am seeking. I am striving. I am in it with all my heart.', 'Vincent Van Gogh'),
  ('r123', 'creative', 123, 'Whatever is done from love always occurs beyond good and evil.', 'Nietzsche (creative tradition)'),
  ('r124', 'creative', 124, 'Write hard and clear about what hurts.', 'Ernest Hemingway'),
  ('r125', 'creative', 125, 'A great artist is always before his time or behind it.', 'George Moore'),
  ('r126', 'creative', 126, 'The earth is art, the photographer is only a witness.', 'Yann Arthus-Bertrand'),
  ('r127', 'creative', 127, 'The artist is not a special kind of person; rather each person is a special kind of artist.', 'Ananda Coomaraswamy'),
  ('r128', 'creative', 128, 'I paint objects as I think them, not as I see them.', 'Pablo Picasso'),
  ('r129', 'creative', 129, 'Creativity is an act of defiance.', 'Twyla Tharp'),
  ('r130', 'creative', 130, 'The job of the artist is always to deepen the mystery.', 'Francis Bacon'),
  ('r131', 'creative', 131, 'A good book is an event in my life.', 'Stendhal'),
  ('r132', 'creative', 132, 'There is nothing more truly artistic than to love people.', 'Vincent Van Gogh'),
  ('r133', 'creative', 133, 'You must write every single day of your life — and never stop thinking about it.', 'Ray Bradbury'),
  ('r134', 'creative', 134, 'Art is the stored honey of the human soul.', 'Theodore Dreiser'),
  ('r135', 'creative', 135, 'Your intuition knows what to write, so get out of the way.', 'Ray Bradbury'),
  ('r136', 'creative', 136, 'The more constraints one imposes, the more one frees oneself.', 'Igor Stravinsky'),
  ('r137', 'creative', 137, 'A dream you dream alone is only a dream. A dream you dream together is reality.', 'John Lennon / Yoko Ono'),
  ('r138', 'creative', 138, 'In art, the hand can never execute anything higher than the heart can inspire.', 'Ralph Waldo Emerson'),
  ('r139', 'creative', 139, 'Creativity is intelligence having fun.', 'Albert Einstein (repeated for emphasis in tradition)'),
  ('r140', 'creative', 140, 'I dream my painting and I paint my dream.', 'Vincent Van Gogh'),
  ('r141', 'creative', 141, 'Every canvas is a journey all its own.', 'Helena Rubinstein'),
  ('r142', 'creative', 142, 'To escape criticism: do nothing, say nothing, be nothing.', 'Elbert Hubbard'),
  ('r143', 'creative', 143, 'Art is not what you make; it is what you make people feel.', 'Unknown'),
  ('r144', 'creative', 144, 'The most important thing in art is The Frame. For painting: literally; for other arts: figuratively — because, without this humble appliance, you can''t know where The Art stops and The Real World begins.', 'Frank Zappa'),
  ('r145', 'creative', 145, 'Find out what you''re afraid of and go live there.', 'Chuck Palahniuk'),
  ('r146', 'creative', 146, 'Every artist dips his brush in his own soul, and paints his own nature into his pictures.', 'Henry Ward Beecher'),
  ('r147', 'creative', 147, 'Prose is architecture, not interior decoration.', 'Ernest Hemingway'),
  ('r148', 'creative', 148, 'The true sign of intelligence is not knowledge but imagination.', 'Albert Einstein'),
  ('r149', 'creative', 149, 'Art must disturb the comfortable and comfort the disturbed.', 'Banksy (attributed)'),
  ('r150', 'creative', 150, 'Art consists of limitation. The most beautiful part of every picture is the frame.', 'G.K. Chesterton'),
  ('r151', 'creative', 151, 'Great artists steal.', 'Pablo Picasso (paraphrased, "Good artists borrow, great artists steal")'),
  ('r152', 'creative', 152, 'Creativity is that marvelous capacity to grasp mutually distinct realities and draw a spark from their juxtaposition.', 'Max Ernst'),
  ('r153', 'creative', 153, 'Books are the mirrors of the soul.', 'Virginia Woolf'),
  ('r154', 'creative', 154, 'The role of the creative leader is not to have all the ideas; it''s to create a culture where everyone can have ideas and feel that they''re valued.', 'Ken Robinson'),
  ('r155', 'creative', 155, 'To be creative means to be in love with life.', 'Osho'),
  ('r156', 'creative', 156, 'Telling the truth in fiction is not the same thing as telling the facts.', 'Unknown'),
  ('r157', 'creative', 157, 'I have no special talent. I am only passionately curious.', 'Albert Einstein'),
  ('r158', 'creative', 158, 'Work gives me a sense of identity; I am whoever I''m inventing.', 'Unknown'),
  ('r159', 'creative', 159, 'Artists don''t get down to work until the pain of working is exceeded by the pain of not working.', 'Stephen DeStaebler'),
  ('r160', 'creative', 160, 'All bad poetry springs from genuine feeling.', 'Oscar Wilde'),
  ('r161', 'creative', 161, 'Imagination is everything. It is the preview of life''s coming attractions.', 'Albert Einstein'),
  ('r162', 'creative', 162, 'Write drunk, edit sober.', 'Ernest Hemingway (attributed)'),
  ('r163', 'creative', 163, 'Good design is obvious. Great design is transparent.', 'Joe Sparano'),
  ('r164', 'creative', 164, 'Work is the best method devised for killing time.', 'William Feather (creative tradition)'),
  ('r165', 'creative', 165, 'Simplicity is the ultimate sophistication.', 'Leonardo da Vinci'),
  ('r166', 'creative', 166, 'The worst thing you write is better than the best thing you didn''t write.', 'Unknown'),
  ('r167', 'creative', 167, 'What we play is life.', 'Louis Armstrong'),
  ('r168', 'creative', 168, 'The purpose of art is washing the dust of daily life off our souls.', 'Pablo Picasso (variant)'),
  ('r169', 'creative', 169, 'If you wait for the perfect moment when all is safe and assured, it may never arrive. Mountains will not be climbed, races won, or lasting happiness achieved.', 'Maurice Chevalier'),
  ('r170', 'creative', 170, 'The first draft of anything is garbage.', 'Ernest Hemingway'),
  ('r171', 'creative', 171, 'Make things as simple as possible but not simpler.', 'Albert Einstein'),
  ('r172', 'creative', 172, 'I try not to write what the reader expects. If I know what they expect, then I know what to subvert.', 'Unknown'),
  ('r173', 'creative', 173, 'Creation is not a hobby. It is a necessity.', 'Unknown'),
  ('r174', 'creative', 174, 'The good ideas are all hammered out in agony by individuals, not floating on the top of the bubbling collective genius.', 'Charles Ives'),
  ('r175', 'creative', 175, 'Music is the shorthand of emotion.', 'Leo Tolstoy'),
  ('r176', 'creative', 176, 'Picasso had a saying: ''Good artists borrow, great artists steal.'' And we have always been shameless about stealing great ideas.', 'Steve Jobs'),
  ('r177', 'creative', 177, 'What''s so great about creativity? It is the whole world condensed.', 'Unknown'),
  ('r178', 'creative', 178, 'The writer''s job is not to judge but to seek to understand.', 'Ernest Hemingway'),
  ('r179', 'creative', 179, 'Art is a wound turned into light.', 'Georges Braque'),
  ('r180', 'creative', 180, 'You can''t exhaust your creativity.', 'Maya Angelou (variant)'),
  ('r181', 'creative', 181, 'Only those who attempt the absurd can achieve the impossible.', 'Albert Einstein'),
  ('r182', 'creative', 182, 'To live a creative life, we must lose our fear of being wrong.', 'Joseph Chilton Pearce'),
  ('r183', 'creative', 183, 'Originality is the fine art of remembering what you hear but forgetting where you heard it.', 'Laurence J. Peter'),
  ('r184', 'creative', 184, 'The most potent muse of all is our own inner child.', 'Stephen Nachmanovitch'),
  ('r185', 'creative', 185, 'The only time I feel alive is when I''m painting.', 'Vincent Van Gogh'),
  ('r186', 'creative', 186, 'A writer''s job is to notice things other people don''t notice.', 'Unknown'),
  ('r187', 'creative', 187, 'Writing is the painting of the voice.', 'Voltaire'),
  ('r188', 'creative', 188, 'Every artist''s greatest masterpiece is the one they haven''t yet created.', 'Unknown'),
  ('r189', 'creative', 189, 'Do not quench your inspiration and your imagination; do not become the slave of your model.', 'Vincent Van Gogh'),
  ('r190', 'creative', 190, 'Art is the only serious thing in the world. And the artist is the only person who is never serious.', 'Oscar Wilde'),
  ('r191', 'creative', 191, 'A deadline is, simply put, optimism in its most kick-ass form.', 'Chris Baty'),
  ('r192', 'creative', 192, 'You don''t write about the horrors of war. No. You write about a kid''s burnt socks lying in the road.', 'Richard Price (creative tradition)'),
  ('r193', 'creative', 193, 'The secret is not following the right path, it''s following that path to the end.', 'Unknown'),
  ('r194', 'creative', 194, 'The worst enemy of creativity is being too comfortable.', 'Unknown'),
  ('r195', 'creative', 195, 'Draw the art you want to see, start the business you want to run, play the music you want to hear, write the books you want to read.', 'Austin Kleon (Steal Like an Artist)'),
  ('r196', 'creative', 196, 'Art is never finished, only abandoned.', 'Leonardo da Vinci'),
  ('r197', 'creative', 197, 'A creative life is an amplified life. It''s a bigger life, a happier life, an expanded life, and a hell of a lot more interesting life.', 'Elizabeth Gilbert'),
  ('r198', 'creative', 198, 'Poetry is what gets lost in translation.', 'Robert Frost'),
  ('r199', 'creative', 199, 'A picture is a poem without words.', 'Horace'),
  ('r200', 'creative', 200, 'The object of the superior man is truth.', 'Confucius (creative tradition)')
